SIMPLE: globule
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Globule
<hw>Glob"ule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>globulus</ets>, dim. of <ets>globus</ets> globe: cf. F.
<ets>globule</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A little globe; a small
particle of matter, of a spherical form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Globules</qex> of snow.</q> <rj><qau>Sir I.
Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These minute <qex>globules</qex> [a mole's eyes] are sunk . . .
deeply in the skull.</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A minute spherical or rounded
structure; as blood, lymph, and pus corpuscles, minute fungi, spores,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A little pill or pellet used by
homeopathists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Globulet</ent>⟦br⟧
